    <p>Tea is an aromatic beverage commonly prepared by pouring hot or
 boiling water over cured leaves of the Camellia sinensis, an evergreen shrub (bush) 
native to East Asia. After water, it is the most widely consumed drink in the world. 
 Tea has a stimulating effect in humans primarily due to its caffeine content.</p>
